Beat cream cheese until fluffy. Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth, add egg and 3 Tbsp. lemon juice; mix well. Pour half the batter into the crust. Combine remaining 1 tsp. lemon juice with preserves in a small bowl. Spoon half the preserves over batter. Pour remaining batter on top. Using a knife, swirl remaining preserves into a decorative pattern. Bake at 300 degrees F for 55 minutes. Cool. Refrigerate leftovers.